#*:: '''After the men's basketball team for China lost at the hands of Greece, [[w:Yao Ming|Yao Ming]] did not become angry.  Instead, he offered his own opinion, which cut right to the heart of the matter, "It will always be like this if we '''operate in a vacuum''', and are forever only playing local league games in our own country.  We need to let them go abroad to compete.  It's not about individual teams going abroad.  Rather, it's about individual team members going abroad and fighting their way onto the teams of other countries.  That's the only way we'll be able raise the level of our basketball as a whole.''  

